[{"_1":2},"llms/mdx",{"_3":4},"data","# fwdx Docs (/docs)\n\n\n\nfwdx [#fwdx]\n\n`fwdx` is a self-hosted tunnel platform for exposing local HTTP services through your own domain.\n\nDocumentation [#documentation]\n\n* [Installation](/docs/installation)\n* [CLI Usage](/docs/cli)\n* [Deployment](/docs/deployment)\n* [Authentication](/docs/authentication)\n* [Architecture / Spec](/docs/architecture)\n\nCurrent Product Scope [#current-product-scope]\n\n* gRPC-based tunnel transport\n* Nginx-friendly deployment model\n* Admin UI and management APIs\n* Detached client tunnel runtime\n* Tunnel request stats and persisted request logs\n\nNext Rewrite Direction [#next-rewrite-direction]\n\nThe platform is being moved toward:\n\n* server-owned control-plane state\n* OIDC-based human authentication\n* separate machine credentials for client agents\n* stronger tunnel observability\n* WebSocket support\n"]
